With the rapid changes on the purchase card requirements, I’d like to clarify the changes on IT purchase procedures for items to be purchased on a purchase card at or below the micro-purchase limit ($3,500). These are NOAA-wide requirements by the Acquisition and Grants Office (AGO) to bring us into compliance with Federal law. The NOAA AGO requirements also apply to non-IT purchases, which are not specifically addressed in this message.

If you need to purchase an IT item on a purchase card at or less than $3,500:
Determine where the IT item will be purchased from. It should be purchased from one of these 5 sources: UNICOR, AbilityOne, GSA Advantage, CSP Enterprises (DOC IT Purchase portal), Enterprise Services Strategic Sourcing Initiatives.
If it is not from one of the vendors through the sources above, Ben Carlson has to do the purchase. Please cc Ben Carlson on the following emails.
Get purchase approval of the IT item from the System Owner (Eugene Burger) by email.
Please cc the card holder you intend to use for the purchase.
State which vendor the item will be purchased from. It should be from one of the sources listed above.

A completed and signed off-portal waiver is required if:
It is an Apple device
An item category (laptop, display, mouse etc.) that is available on the DOC IT purchase portal is being purchased at another vendor.
Following the approval from Eugene Burger
If the device is one of these items, CNSD will guide the purchase of the device. Please submit a Footprints ticket with an IT item specifications screen capture or link to the shopping cart.

These IT items have to be purchased through CNSD:
All computers, to include
Laptops, Desktops, Rack mounted servers, Network equipment,
Any equipment that will be connected to any NOAA network.

For other IT-related items, any purchase card holder can purchase the item if it is through one of these sources: UNICOR, AbilityOne, GSA Advantage, CSP Enterprises (DOC IT Purchase portal), Enterprise Services Strategic Sourcing Initiatives.
